WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.196 --> 00:00:11.416
 Tailor tack presser No. 7 

00:00:12.280 --> 00:00:19.280
 Usually, it is used for marking to make a tack on the fabric, but it is also used for decorative sewing, fringes, and phagoting. 

00:00:20.060 --> 00:00:23.940
 Do the end decoration sewing. 

00:00:24.700 --> 00:00:27.900
 Attach the presser to the sewing machine. 

00:00:29.165 --> 00:00:34.565
 Makes the sewing machine recognize the presser (varies depending on the model). 

00:00:35.906 --> 00:00:49.326
 Select zigzag stitching, and set the swing width to 5.5 and the feed length to 0.3 (satin stitch). Set the upper thread tension to 0.75. 

00:00:52.400 --> 00:00:59.080
 Prepare 2 sheets of properly ironed fabric and set them from the left and right of the presser. 

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:07.930
 Lower the presser using the knee presser lifter. At that time, set the center guide of the presser to be properly between the two sheets of fabric. 

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:13.980
 While sewing, use your hand to make the fabric run parallel. 

00:01:18.486 --> 00:01:23.066
 After sewing, pull the fabric left and right to flatten it. 

00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:29.920
 Remove the 7th presser and attach the 20C presser. 

00:01:32.858 --> 00:01:39.038
 Makes the sewing machine recognize the presser (varies depending on the model). 

00:01:43.212 --> 00:01:50.212
 Select straight stitching and increase the feed length to 3.5. 

00:01:52.512 --> 00:01:58.952
 I will sew the center of the part that I opened earlier. Then the previous thread will be put together. 

00:02:03.493 --> 00:02:08.453
 You may add decorative stitching to the left and right edges as you like. 

00:02:09.118 --> 00:02:13.758
 I was able to sew beautiful ends. 

00:02:15.593 --> 00:02:19.313
 Make a fringe. 

00:02:20.416 --> 00:02:28.176
 Please make the upper thread and the lower thread stand out in different colors. At the end of sewing, the lower thread is pulled out. 

00:02:28.967 --> 00:02:44.927
 Select zigzag stitching, and set the swing width to 5.5 and the feed length to 0.3 (satin stitch). Set the upper thread tension to 0.75. 

00:02:51.110 --> 00:02:58.030
 Remove the 20C presser and attach the 7th presser to the sewing machine. 

00:03:00.280 --> 00:03:05.060
 Makes the sewing machine recognize the presser (varies depending on the model). 

00:03:07.631 --> 00:03:12.371
 Set the end of the fabric and the stabilizer from the left and right. 

00:03:12.588 --> 00:03:17.768
 Lower the presser with the knee presser lifter. At this time, make sure that the center guide of the presser comes between the dough and the stabilizer. 

00:03:18.120 --> 00:03:21.320
 I will sew evenly left and right. 

00:03:30.055 --> 00:03:36.235
 After sewing, pull the fabric and the stabilizer from side to side. 

00:03:42.339 --> 00:03:49.779
 Turn the fabric over and carefully pull the bobbin thread carefully. 

00:03:53.285 --> 00:03:59.665
 Remove the 7th presser and attach the 20C presser to the sewing machine. 

00:04:04.731 --> 00:04:11.271
 Makes the sewing machine recognize the presser (varies depending on the model). 

00:04:12.003 --> 00:04:18.643
 Select 419 decorative stitching or similar decorative stitching. 

00:04:20.520 --> 00:04:26.180
 Bring up the information screen and flip the pattern left and right. 

00:04:27.232 --> 00:04:32.472
 Set the stabilizer under the dough. 

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:43.300
 Sew along the top of the fringe. 

00:04:46.131 --> 00:04:52.511
 Slowly remove the two sheets of stabilizing paper carefully. 

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:09.740
 I could easily make a fringe at the end of the fabric. 

